{"link_name": "DB4bix", "type": "Module", "OS": "", "vendor": "", "minZabbVer": "2.2.x", "link_desc": "<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 16px;\">DB4bix is the DB monitoring tool for Zabbix. It behaves like an active <span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 600;\">Zabbix Proxy</span> by getting configuration from Zabbix Server and sending the results back.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />It was initially based on <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #4078c0;\" href=\"http://www.smartmarmot.com/product/dbforbix/\">DBforBix by SmartMarmot</a> and forked from version <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #4078c0;\" href=\"https://sourceforge.net/projects/dbforbix/files/?source=navbar\">2.1-beta from sourceforge</a>.</p>\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.25; padding-bottom: 0.3em; border-bottom: 1px solid #eeeeee; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol';\"><a id=\"user-content-key-featuresaims-of-db4bix\" class=\"anchor\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #4078c0; float: left; padding-right: 4px; margin-left: -20px; line-height: 1;\" href=\"https://github.com/vagabondan/db4bix/wiki#key-featuresaims-of-db4bix\"></a>Key features/aims of DB4bix</h2>\n<ol style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-left: 2em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 16px;\">\n<ol style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-left: 2em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 16px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Closest integration with Zabbix Web interface. You can control DB monitoring with DB4bix just like it were ordinary Zabbix Proxy, and as a consequence, updates its configuration and behaviour on the fly.</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.25em;\">DB4bix supports Low Level Discovery, multirow and multicolumn selects from databases. This feature greatly improves effeciency of DB monitoring.</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.25em;\">One instance of DB4bix can handle several different Zabbix Servers with different hosts/items configurations at a time, i.e. it can be a Zabbix Proxy for multiple Zabbix Servers.</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.25em;\">DB4bix understands and resolves Host/Templates macros (i.e. {$DSN}, {$ANY_OTHER_STUFF}, etc.)</li>\n</ol>\n</ol>", "features": "Database Monitor", "address": "", "city": "", "state": "", "country": "", "postcode": "", "telephone": "", "fax": "", "email": "", "website": "https://github.com/vagabondan/db4bix/wiki", "price": 0, "link_hits": 8625, "link_votes": 1, "link_rating": 5, "link_featured": null, "link_created": "2017-01-08 13:32:28", "link_modified": "2017-01-08 14:57:29", "link_visited": 2496, "publish_up": "2017-01-08 13:32:28", "publish_down": "0000-00-00 00:00:00", "metakey": "", "metadesc": "", "1.8": "", "2.0": "", "2.2": "", "2.4": "", "3.0": "", "3.2": "", "3.4": "", "4.0": "", "4.2": "", "4.4": "", "5.0": "", "5.2": "", "tags": "DB, Oracle, MySQL, PostgreSQL, Zabbix Proxy", "author": "Andrey Denisov", "user_id": 1536, "link_id": 718, "cat_id": "111", "internal_notes": "", "lat": 0, "lng": 0, "zoom": ""}